  "name": "Poisoner's Ring",
  "meta": "[Ring, varies (requires attunement)](https://www.dndbeyond.com/magic-items/7278391-poisoners-ring)",
  "desc": "This ring looks to be a mundane ring, however on closer inspection, a hidden hatch slides away, allowing one to hide all kinds of illicit substances.\n\nUncommon (Malignant) : While attuned to this ring, you gain a bonus to the saving throw DCs of your poisons. In addition, while attuned to this ring, you gain advantage on dexterity (sleight of hand) checks.\n\nRare (Toxic): The Toxic ring has the Malignant property. In addition, the ring has 4 charges. As a reaction you may spend a charge and impose disadvantage on one constitution saving throw made to resist the effects of a poison. You regain all expended charges at the end of a long rest. The bonus to the DC of your poison saves increases by +2, instead of +1\n\nVery Rare (Fatal): The fatal ring has the effects of the toxic ring and the malignant ring. Additionally, when determining the damage of your poisons, the damage die increases by one. The bonus to the DC of your poison saves increases by +3, instead of +2.\n\nDamage die is as follows: 1d4>1d6>1d8>1d10>1d12>1d20\n\nThe bonus is determined by the ring's rarity."
}